Class SFMT19937

java.lang.Object
  SFMT19937

public class SFMT19937
extends java.lang.Object

An adapation of SFMT (SIMD oriented Fast Mersenne Twister) version 1.3 by Mutsuo Saito (Hiroshima University) and Makoto Matsumoto (Hiroshima University). This adapation supports only the period 219937 − 1; the original supports some longer and shorter periods.

Field Detail

MEXP

public static final int MEXP
Mersenne Exponent. The period of the sequence is a multiple of 2MEXP − 1. If you adapt this code to support a different exponent, you must change many of the other constants here as well; consult the original C code.

fillArray

public void fillArray(int[] array,
                      int elems)
Fills the given array with the specified number of pseudorandom 32-bit integers. The specified number of elements must be a multiple of four.

Parameters:
array - array to fill.
elems - the number of elements of array (starting at index zero) to fill; subsequent elements are not modified.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if elems is greater than the length of array, or is less than N32, or is not a multiple of 4.
